= The Relationship Between Islam , Īmān (Faith), and Iḥsān (Excellence) 

== When mentioned together:

When all three terms are mentioned together, each has its specific meaning:

- *Islām refers to:* Outward actions (such as prayer, fasting, etc.)
- *Īmān (Faith) refers to:* Matters of belief in the unseen (such as belief in
  Allāh, angels, and divine decree)
- *Iḥsān (Excellence) refers to:* The highest level of the religion.

== When mentioned separately:

When each of these terms is mentioned individually:

If Islām is mentioned alone, Īmān is included within it.

If Īmān is mentioned alone, Islam is included within it.

If Iḥsān is mentioned alone, both Islam and Imān are included within it.